author: Justin Harp
title: TV show ratings: The Good Wife returns to match its spring finale on Sunday - The Simpsons US TV -
text: The Good Wife matched its spring finale with its return to CBS on Sunday (October 4), according to Nielsen figures.The legal drama earned 1.2 (9.37m) at 9pm on CBS, while Madam Secretary and CSI: Cyber dipped to 1.5 (11.93m) at 8pm and 1.0 (7.02m) at 10pm. © CBS NBC won the key 18-49 demographic on Sunday (October 4) with 6.3.Sunday Night Football on the Peacock Network soared to 7.2 (20.17m) at 8pm.Fox's The Simpsons reached 2.6 (6m) at 8pm, Brooklyn Nine-Nine hit 1.9 (4.1m) at 8.30pm, Family Guy garnered 1.7 (3.63m) at 9pm and The Last Man On Earth interested 1.5 (3.3m) at 9.30pm. © ABC ABC's Blood & Oil dropped two-tenths of a point to 1.2 (5.19m) at 9pm, following Once Upon a Time averaging 1.8 (5.33m) at 8pm.At 10pm on ABC, Quantico was steady with 1.9 (6.94m).
